						               													<description>This is a small expansion for the base-game Shanghaien. It is based in an extra &amp;quot;dirty tricks&amp;quot; card called &amp;quot;Send to the sharks / Exchange&amp;quot;.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Every player gets one at the beginning of the game. He can use it one time during the game like every other &amp;quot;dirty tricks&amp;quot; card.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Using it he can choose between two actions:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;- &amp;ldquo;Send to the sharks&amp;rdquo;: The player flips the card of the tavern onto which he has added a die in the same&amp;#10;turn onto its back side. When the cards are distributed, cards of the tavern which are flipped over are&amp;#10;removed from the game regardless of dice added onto them. Nevertheless dice added to a flipped card still&amp;#10;count as tie-breakers for adjacent cards which are not turned over. The &amp;ldquo;dirty tricks&amp;rdquo;-card is removed from&amp;#10;the game after usage.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;- &amp;ldquo;Exchange&amp;rdquo;: The player takes one of his own dice he has added to a card of the tavern in a previous turn&amp;#10;back to his supply. Then he adds both dice he has rolled in that turn onto the corresponding cards of&amp;#10;the tavern. This action can only be performed if the player has added at least one die to the tavern in a&amp;#10;previous turn. The &amp;ldquo;dirty tricks&amp;rdquo;-card is removed from the game after usage.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;You can download the cards here:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;http://www.michaelschacht.net/p/shangXPUS2.pdf (english, letter)&amp;#10;http://www.michaelschacht.net/p/shangXP2.pdf (german, DINA4)&amp;#10;http://www.michaelschacht.net/p/shangXPE2.pdf (spanish)&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
